<br>
&quot;I have read a lot about the new raiding functions. And read, and read. And read the naysayers and the propentents both. But has anyone stopped to think that this may create a new way to play EQ? <br>
<br>
Could this possibly be the dawn of a new day? Let's take for instance the DS Hopper/Tribal Caves. This can accomodate a few groups of appropriate level... <br>
<br>
So could all the groups that are competing cutthroat style for spawns there agree to disagree? Even though the exp might be a bit worse per capita, could all the people there agree that instead of competing for spawns, that they should instead work together? <br>
<br>
All strive to work together and kill EVERYTHING in site. Kill it as soon as it spawns and keep everything perma dead, save for a few scant seconds. <br>
<br>
Seems like a good idea to me, and it seems that it would do a good deal to build goodwill toward your fellow man. <br>
<br>
Yeah group dynamics would be a bit FUBAR. But given time people would adapt. And with a whole chat devoted to that camp, all players would be able to communicate and call for help, etc.. <br>
<br>
Seems to me that a whole new dynamic is opening in the EQ world. It's up to us to take advantage of it&quot; <p>Tortevahl Skorned<br>
